org.hswgt.teachingbox.core.ml.lwlr

Class LocallyWeightedLinearRegression

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.hswgt.teachingbox.core.ml.lwlr.LocallyWeightedLinearRegression

  • public class LocallyWeightedLinearRegression
extends Object
    Memory-based approximation by Locally Weighted Linear Regression (lazy learning). Uses the WEKA (Univ. of Waikato) (http://www.cs.waikato.ac.nz/ml/weka/) class LWL (Locally Weighted Learning) with Linear Regression as local approximation, a linear weighting function (by default) and a KDTree for nearest neighbor search. For more information about Locally Weighted Learning, please read C. Atkeson, A. Moore, S. Schaal (1996). Locally Weighted Learning. AI Review...
    Author:
    Richard Cubek

      • setWeightingKernel

        public void setWeightingKernel(int kernel)
        Set the weighting kernel being used to determine the weights of the k nearest neighbours. Possible choices are LINEAR, EPANECHNIKOV, TRICUBE, CONSTANT. The use of GAUSSIAN or INVERSE (LWL in WEKA) does not work locally (already annotated, will maybe be changed in near future). Default value: LINEAR (performed very good in tests).
        Parameters:
        kernel - The kernel method to use.
